              <span class="text-red-400">✗</span>
              <span>Applies fix, runs compiler, new errors appear</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-red-400">✗</span>
              <span>Repeat until lucky or out of tokens</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-gray-900 border border-repair-500/30">
          <div class="text-repair-400 text-lg font-semibold mb-3">With ts-repair</div>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-400">
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-repair-400">✓</span>
              <span>Agent receives verified repair plan</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-repair-400">✓</span>
              <span>Every fix proven to reduce errors</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-repair-400">✓</span>
              <span>Fixes ordered for maximum impact</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-3">
              <span class="text-repair-400">✓</span>
              <span>Apply confidently, no guesswork</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Disposition Categories Summary (Compact) -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-gray-900/50">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Explicit Uncertainty</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-center mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        ts-repair classifies each diagnostic by disposition, surfacing uncertainty explicitly. It never silently applies unsafe fixes.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-xs font-mono bg-repair-500/20 text-repair-400 border border-repair-500/30">AutoFixable</span>
