  <!-- Early Benchmark Results -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Early Benchmark Results</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-center mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Claude Code fixing TypeScript errors in Zod v4 &mdash; with and without ts-repair.
      </p>

      <!-- Caveat Banner -->
      <div class="mb-8 p-4 rounded-lg bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/30 text-center">
        <p class="text-amber-400 text-sm">
          <strong>Early results from a single benchmark.</strong> We seeded 206 type errors into Zod v4 and measured Claude Code's repair process. Results will vary by project complexity and error types.
          <a href="https://github.com/ts-repair/ts-repair/blob/main/docs/benchmarking/zod-benchmark-01.md" class="underline hover:text-amber-300 ml-1">Full methodology &rarr;</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Framing Paragraph -->
      <div class="mb-10 p-5 rounded-lg bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800">
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <strong class="text-white">Why typo-style root causes matter:</strong> A single mistyped import or renamed symbol can cascade into dozens or hundreds of downstream diagnostics. These high-fan-out errors are common after refactors, dependency updates, and code generation &mdash; exactly when agents need help most.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          <strong class="text-white">The dominant cost driver</strong> in agent-assisted repair is repeated context re-ingestion: each compile&ndash;check&ndash;fix cycle forces the agent to re-read error output, re-analyze, and re-plan. ts-repair's efficiency gain comes from <strong class="text-white">collapsing six verification rounds into one</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm italic">
          This benchmark demonstrates the type of efficiency gain made possible by eliminating redundant compile cycles; absolute results vary by workload.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Metrics Grid -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-repair-400 mb-2">52%</div>
          <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-1">Cost Reduction</div>
          <div class="text-gray-500 text-xs">$2.55 &rarr; $1.23</div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-repair-400 mb-2">63%</div>
          <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-1">Fewer Tokens</div>
          <div class="text-gray-500 text-xs">3.58M &rarr; 1.32M input</div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-repair-400 mb-2">32%</div>
          <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-1">Faster</div>
          <div class="text-gray-500 text-xs">13m 23s &rarr; 9m 6s</div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-gray-900 border border-gray-800 text-center">
          <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-repair-400 mb-2">6&rarr;1</div>
          <div class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-1">Repair Rounds</div>
          <div class="text-gray-500 text-xs">Compile-check-fix cycles</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Secondary stat -->
      <div class="text-center text-gray-400 text-sm mb-8">
        <span class="text-repair-400 font-semibold">67% fewer bash commands</span> (27 &rarr; 9) &mdash; less compile-check-fix churn
      </div>

      <!-- Future Benchmarks Note -->
      <div class="text-center text-gray-500 text-sm border-t border-gray-800 pt-6">
        <strong class="text-gray-400">What's next:</strong> We're building an automated benchmark harness for cross-project testing (React, Express, etc.) and non-typo workloads (generic constraints, inference failures, overloads).
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Not Guesswork Section -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-gray-900/50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Not Guesswork. Not AI Hallucinations.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        ts-repair does not invent fixes. It does not use LLMs to generate code.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
        Every fix is verified by the TypeScript compiler. Fixes are only surfaced if they
        <strong class="text-white">strictly reduce the error set</strong>. If a candidate fix
        introduces new errors or fails to resolve any, it is discarded &mdash; never presented to the agent.
      </p>
    </div>
